Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Meanwhile Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces). Trim the @carrot{1}, then quarter lengthways (no need to peel). Chop widthways into small pieces. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the bell pepper on a #baking tray{} and drizzle with @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then mix to coat the pepper, spread evenly and roast on the top shelf of your oven until starting to char and soften, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g}, breaking it up with a #spoon{}. Cook, stirring frequently until brown all over, ~{3-4%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Once the beef is browned, add the onion and carrot and cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook for a further ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @red wine stock paste{28%g} and @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1}. Bring to the boil and reduce the heat to medium. Cook until slightly thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Once the peppers have roasted, stir them into the sauce and season to taste. TIP: Add a splash of water if it's thickened too much.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. Break up the @gnocchi{300%g} and add into the #pan{} with the ragu. Stir well and pour into an #ovenproof dish{}. Sprinkle over the grated Cheddar and grated @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated). Grill on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown and bubbling, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once the bake is golden and bubbling, carefully remove from the oven. Share between your plates and enjoy!